# Spring Semester Plans

Primary Goal: Finish the current prosthetic hand setup and integrate the DC motors into the system. 

- We should have nearly every part ready to fully wire everything -  whatever we don’t have, let me know and I will order it so we can get this part of the project done ASAP.
- Integrate with code and ensure we have similar function to before - 1’s are open and 0 is close.

Next steps: After wiring, solder everything into perfboards OR create a custom PCB that will fit all components seamlessly. That way we don’t have such a big clutter within the hand.

*Side project: We have a joystick from LHNT - I was hoping we could wire this in as a simple control mechanism to test open and close. It is more to test if actuation is working properly and not have to rely on UDP signals (which has been an issue for is).*

If all this gets done and we are able to integrate with ML, then we can potentially move on to infrared and pressure sensors.

- Infrared sensors would be for detecting an object that is nearby and sort of ‘slowing’ the close motion to not slam the fingers on the object
- Pressure sensors would be to measure the force applied when grabbing objects and allow us to quantify how much our hand can lift.
